&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Under the &lt;strong&gt;SLKIC vertical of Khelo India&lt;/strong&gt;, the Government of India has adopted &lt;strong&gt;6 Kendriya Vidyalayas&lt;/strong&gt; in partnership with the Kendriya Vidyalaya Sangathan (KVS).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Khelo India&lt;/strong&gt; is a national programme aimed at promoting sports and fitness in India. It focuses on developing sports infrastructure and nurturing talent at the grassroots level.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The adoption of Kendriya Vidyalayas under the &lt;strong&gt;SLKIC vertical&lt;/strong&gt; intends to integrate sports into the academic curriculum, ensuring holistic development of students.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;SLKIC (School Level Khelo India Centre)&lt;/strong&gt; initiative serves as a platform for identifying and nurturing sports talent within schools, which are equipped with proper facilities and training programs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This partnership between &lt;strong&gt;KVS and Khelo India&lt;/strong&gt; emphasizes the Government&amp;#39;s commitment to promoting sports at the school level and ensuring that students are provided with adequate resources for sporting excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Khelo India Programme:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Launched in &lt;strong&gt;2018&lt;/strong&gt; by the Ministry of Youth Affairs and Sports to promote sports culture in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The program aims to encourage young talent and provide them with financial assistance and training facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It includes initiatives like the &lt;strong&gt;Khelo India Youth Games&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Khelo India University Games&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Khelo India School Centres&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The scheme offers up to &lt;strong&gt;₹5 lakh per year&lt;/strong&gt; to selected athletes for training and development.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kendriya Vidyalaya Sangathan (KVS):&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;KVS was established in &lt;strong&gt;1963&lt;/strong&gt; under the Ministry of Education to provide high-quality education to the children of transferable Central Government employees.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;KVS schools are known for their uniform curriculum, excellent infrastructure, and co-curricular activities, including sports.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;There are more than &lt;strong&gt;1,200 Kendriya Vidyalayas&lt;/strong&gt; across India, providing education to lakhs of students.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SLKIC (School Level Khelo India Centre):&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The SLKIC initiative is part of the Khelo India mission to identify and develop sports talent at the school level.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Schools adopted under this program are provided with basic sports infrastructure, equipment, and expert coaching.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The centers focus on various sports disciplines, ensuring that students receive specialized training in sports like athletics, swimming, football, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sports Development in India:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;India has been actively promoting sports culture through schemes such as &lt;strong&gt;Khelo India&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Target Olympic Podium Scheme (TOPS)&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Fit India Movement&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The government is investing in grassroots sports development and high-performance training for elite athletes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Sports infrastructure like stadiums and training centers are being developed in collaboration with public and private organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objective of Khelo India:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;To create a strong framework for sports development in the country.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;To identify and nurture sports talent at the grassroots level.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;To integrate sports into the academic system and promote physical fitness among students.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role of KVS in Sports Development:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;KVS schools have been actively participating in national and regional sports tournaments.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;By adopting Kendriya Vidyalayas under Khelo India, the government aims to maximize the reach of sports programs and training facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;The inspector will convene a meeting of his juniors.&amp;nbsp;.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The structure of the given sentence is as follows:
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object + shall/will not + have + been + V3 + by + subject. (Passive Voice)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Subject + shall/will not + have + V3 + object. (Active Voice)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The subject&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;A meeting of his juniors&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;the inspector&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be put in place of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the object&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be put in place of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the subject.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;will be convened&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;will convene&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Lastly, the conjunction&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;by&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be removed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 2.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The inspector will convene a meeting of his juniors.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;Transformation of Infinitives&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;: The structure of it is&amp;nbsp;as follows:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + is/am/are/was/were/has/have/had + to + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ Object.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject(Objective case) + is/am/are/was/were/has/have/had + to + be + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;+ by+ object(subjective case).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Your child is to learn chess. (Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Chess is to be learnt by your child. (Passive Voice)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

