&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Morocco&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ibn-Battuta:-&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ibn Battuta, born as&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Abū ʿAbd Allāh Muḥammad ibn ʿAbd Allāh al-Lawātī al-Ṭanjī ibn Baṭṭūṭah&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;on&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;February 24&lt;/span&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;1304&lt;/span&gt;, in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Tangier&lt;/span&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Morocco&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;He is lauded as one of the greatest medieval Muslim explorers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Over a period of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;30 years&lt;/span&gt;, he traveled an estimated&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;75,000 miles&lt;/span&gt;, significantly more than his&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;contemporary Marco&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Polo&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ibn Battuta started his travels in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;1325&lt;/span&gt;, setting off from Morocco with the aim of performing Hajj, the pilgrimage to the holy city of Mecca.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He died in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;late 1360s or 1377 in Morocco.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;China:-&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-sourcepos=&quot;3:1-3:125&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;It is considered as the cradle of ancient civilizations,&amp;nbsp;boasting 5,000 years of history known for influential inventions like gunpowder and paper.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-sourcepos=&quot;4:1-4:89&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;It has evolved from dynasties to the modern communist state,&amp;nbsp;with a booming economy and global influence.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-sourcepos=&quot;5:1-6:0&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;It has rich cultural heritage evident in traditions,&amp;nbsp;architecture,&amp;nbsp;and diverse regional cuisines.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Greece:-&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;It is the birthplace of democracy,&amp;nbsp;philosophy,&amp;nbsp;and the Olympics,&amp;nbsp;shaping Western thought and culture.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-sourcepos=&quot;10:1-10:86&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;It has picturesque islands and ancient ruins like the Acropolis attract tourists worldwide.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-sourcepos=&quot;11:1-11:38&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;It faces contemporary challenges within the European Union,&amp;nbsp;yet retains its unique spirit and resilient character.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Persia (modern Iran):&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-sourcepos=&quot;15:1-15:9&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;It is the home to the vast Achaemenid Empire,&amp;nbsp;leaving behind architectural wonders like Persepolis.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-sourcepos=&quot;16:1-16:100&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;It is a blend of ancient traditions and Islamic faith,&amp;nbsp;known for vibrant carpets,&amp;nbsp;poetry,&amp;nbsp;and hospitality.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-sourcepos=&quot;17:1-17:116&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px;&quot;&gt;It faces complex geopolitical situations but remains a significant cultural and historical center in the Middle East.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Swadeshi Movement&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;During the&lt;strong&gt; Swadeshi Movement&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;Vande Mataram&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; became a popular song of people.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Swadeshi movement began in&lt;strong&gt; 1905&lt;/strong&gt; with the &lt;strong&gt;Viceroy of India, Lord Curzon&lt;/strong&gt;, partitioning Bengal and continued until 1911.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This was the strongest in &lt;strong&gt;Bengal &lt;/strong&gt;and was also recognized in India as the&lt;strong&gt; Vandemataram Movement&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Among the movement&amp;#39;s various forms of struggle, it was the boycott of foreign-made goods that encountered the greatest visible success on the practical and popular levels.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Boycotts and public burning of foreign clothes, picketing of shops selling foreign goods, all became common in remote corners of Bengal as well as in many major cities and towns across the country.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Another form of mass mobilization widely used by the Swadeshi movement was the corps of volunteers (samitis).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Ashwini Kumar Dutt, a school teacher, set up the Swadesh Bandhab Samiti in Barisal which&amp;nbsp;was the best-known volunteer organization of all of them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Shivaji &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;Ganapati festivals&lt;/strong&gt; in Western India (Maharashtra) were organized by &lt;strong&gt;Lokmanya Tilak&lt;/strong&gt; to spread the swadeshi message and boycott movements among the masses.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The Swadeshi and boycott movements placed great emphasis on &amp;#39; Atmasakti &amp;#39; or self-reliance as a means of reasserting national dignity in different fields.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tibetan Plateau&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Tibetan Plateau is the &lt;strong&gt;highest and biggest plateau on Earth&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is popularly known as the &lt;strong&gt;roof of the world.&lt;/strong&gt; It is located in &lt;strong&gt;southwestern China.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It has resulted from a &lt;strong&gt;collision between two tectonic plates about 55 million years ago&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Other names of this plateau are &lt;strong&gt;Plateau of Tibet, Chinese (Pinyin) Qingzang Gaoyuan or (Wade-Giles romanization) Ch&amp;rsquo;ing-Tsang Kao-yuan, also called Tibetan Highlands or Qinghai-Tibet Plateau.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The plateau, which has an area of about &lt;strong&gt;965,000 square miles (2,500,000 square km), is a region of tangled mountains and uplands that are generally above 13,000 to 15,000 feet (4,000 to 5,000 meters) in elevation&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mount Everest (Qomolangma Feng), rising 29,035 feet (8,850 meters) above sea level on the China-Nepal border, is the world&amp;rsquo;s highest peak of the world.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Several rivers start from this plateau and flow eastwards and southwards.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The eastwards flowing rivers are the &lt;strong&gt;Yellow River, Yangtze, and the Mekong&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The southward flowing ones include the &lt;strong&gt;Salween, the Indus River in India, and the Irrawaddy River in Burma.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kosi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Kosi River is often referred to as the &amp;quot;Sorrow of Bihar&amp;quot; due to its frequent flooding, which causes significant loss of life and property in the region.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Originating from the Himalayas in Nepal, the Kosi River carries a large amount of silt, leading to unpredictable changes in its course.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Its flooding has historically devastated agricultural lands and displaced thousands of people in northern Bihar.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The river flows into the Ganga and spans several districts in Bihar, including Supaul, Saharsa, and Madhepura.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Efforts to control the flooding include the construction of embankments, but these have not been entirely successful due to the river&amp;#39;s dynamic nature.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flooding Dynamics:&lt;/strong&gt; The Kosi River is a transboundary river that originates in Nepal, making flood management complex due to international coordination requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Siltation:&lt;/strong&gt; The river carries immense amounts of silt from the Himalayas, which is deposited in the plains, altering its course unpredictably.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kosi Barrage:&lt;/strong&gt; Built in 1963 near Birpur in Bihar, the Kosi Barrage was designed to reduce flooding, but its effectiveness has been limited.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Environmental Impact:&lt;/strong&gt; Frequent floods result in soil erosion, destruction of biodiversity, and challenges in sustainable agricultural practices in the region.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Historical Context:&lt;/strong&gt; The Kosi&amp;#39;s floods have been documented since ancient times, and it remains one of the most challenging rivers to manage in the Indian subcontinent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Only 1 is Correct&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement 1:&lt;/strong&gt; The athlete attains maximum momentum by running on the runway before take-off.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In the long jump, the runway phase is crucial as the athlete builds maximum speed and momentum.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The purpose of this phase is to ensure the athlete achieves the highest horizontal velocity before take-off.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This momentum directly influences the distance covered during the jump. &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, statement 1 is correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement 2:&lt;/strong&gt; During take-off, the athlete pushes off with the weaker foot to maintain balance.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This statement is incorrect because the athlete typically uses their stronger or dominant foot for the take-off.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The take-off foot provides the required explosive force to propel the body upward and forward.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Using the weaker foot would compromise the efficiency and distance of the jump. &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, statement 2 is incorrect.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In conclusion, only the first statement is correct, making the correct answer &lt;strong&gt;Only 1 is Correct&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Phases of the Long Jump:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The long jump consists of four main phases: &lt;strong&gt;runway, take-off, flight, and landing&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;During the &lt;strong&gt;runway phase&lt;/strong&gt;, athletes aim to reach maximum controllable speed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In the &lt;strong&gt;take-off phase&lt;/strong&gt;, the athlete converts horizontal momentum into vertical lift using their stronger foot.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;flight phase&lt;/strong&gt; involves maintaining balance and posture mid-air to optimize distance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;landing phase&lt;/strong&gt; is critical for maximizing the jump distance and ensuring a clean landing without loss of points.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Factors Influencing Long Jump Performance:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speed:&lt;/strong&gt; High runway speed is essential for generating momentum.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strength:&lt;/strong&gt; Explosive leg power determines the quality of the take-off.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technique:&lt;/strong&gt; Proper posture, arm movement, and body control during the flight and landing phases significantly affect performance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consistency:&lt;/strong&gt; Accurate placement of the take-off foot on the board ensures legality and efficiency of the jump.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Training for Long Jump:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Athletes focus on &lt;strong&gt;sprinting, strength training, and plyometric exercises&lt;/strong&gt; to improve explosive power and speed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&lt;strong&gt;Practice drills include runway repetitions, jump simulations, and landing techniques.
		&lt;li&gt;Coaches emphasize proper biomechanics to ensure efficient energy transfer during take-off.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/li&lt;strong&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;International Long Jump Records:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;men&amp;#39;s world record&lt;/strong&gt; in the long jump is held by &lt;strong&gt;Mike Powell&lt;/strong&gt; (USA) with a jump of &lt;strong&gt;8.95 meters&lt;/strong&gt;, achieved in &lt;strong&gt;1991&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;women&amp;#39;s world record&lt;/strong&gt; is held by &lt;strong&gt;Galina Chistyakova&lt;/strong&gt; (USSR) with a jump of &lt;strong&gt;7.52 meters&lt;/strong&gt;, achieved in &lt;strong&gt;1988&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Olympic Long Jump:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The long jump has been part of the Olympic Games since their modern inception in &lt;strong&gt;1896&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Notable athletes include &lt;strong&gt;Carl Lewis&lt;/strong&gt;, who won &lt;strong&gt;four consecutive Olympic gold medals&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;1984 to 1996&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Biomechanics of Long Jump:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The jump relies on the principles of &lt;strong&gt;kinematics and dynamics&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Efficient energy transfer from horizontal to vertical motion is crucial for achieving maximum distance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Body posture during flight affects air resistance and overall performance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
